  "prompt_text": "Design a memorial for victims of a natural disaster. Address both the structural engineering and the emotional needs of survivors.",
  "response_text": "**Memorial Design: \"Resilience and Hope\"**\n\n**Structural Engineering:**\n\nThe memorial, titled \"Resilience and Hope,\" is designed to be a symbol of strength, unity, and hope for the community affected by the natural disaster. The structure will be built on a raised platform, approximately 50 feet in diameter and 10 feet high, to ensure it remains visible and accessible from a distance.\n\nThe foundation will be a sturdy concrete base, designed to withstand extreme weather conditions and potential future disasters. The main structure will be made of reclaimed wood, sourced from trees that were not affected by the disaster. The wood will be carefully selected and arranged to create a sense of movement and fluidity, representing the resilience of the community.\n\nThe memorial will have three main components:\n\n1.  **The Wave Wall**: A 20-foot-tall wall made of reclaimed wood, featuring a series of undulating waves that evoke the power and fury of the natural disaster. The waves will be designed to appear as if they are moving upwards, symbolizing the community's determination to rise above the tragedy.\n2.  **The Light Tree**: A 20-foot-tall metal tree, adorned with hundreds of LED lights that will be programmed to simulate a sunrise and sunset pattern. The lights will be a reminder of the hope and new beginnings that emerge after a disaster.\n3.  **The Memorial Plaza**: A flat, open space where visitors can gather, reflect, and pay their respects. The plaza will feature a large, etched stone slab with the names of the victims, a dedication to the community, and a quote that inspires hope and resilience.\n\n**Emotional Needs of Survivors:**\n\nTo address the emotional needs of survivors, the memorial will incorporate several design elements:\n\n1.  **Comfort Zones**: The memorial will feature several comfortable seating areas, where visitors can sit, reflect, and share their stories. These zones will be designed to provide a sense of calm and peace.\n2.  **Interactive Elements**: A series of interactive displays will be placed throughout the memorial, allowing visitors to share their personal stories, memories, and reflections. These displays will be designed to create a sense of connection and community.\n3.  **Artistic Expression**: A designated area will be allocated for community members to express their emotions through art, music, or other forms of creative expression. This will provide a safe space for visitors to process their grief and find healing.\n4.  **Personalized Memorials**: Visitors will be able to create personalized memorials for their loved ones, which will be displayed in a designated area. This will provide a sense of ownership and closure for those who have lost loved ones.\n\n**Sustainability and Maintenance:**\n\nThe memorial will be designed with sustainability in mind, incorporating features such as:\n\n1.  **Rainwater Harvesting**: A system will be installed to collect and reuse rainwater for irrigation and other non-potable purposes.\n2. ",
